msgid "Circular Descriptives"
msgstr "Deskriptif Melingkar"

msgid "Valid"
msgstr "Valid"

msgid "Missing"
msgstr "Hilang"

msgid "Mean Direction"
msgstr "Arah Rerata"

msgid "Mean Resultant Length"
msgstr "Panjang Resultan Rerata"

msgid "Median"
msgstr "Median"

msgid "Standard Deviation"
msgstr "Deviasi Standar"

msgid "Variance"
msgstr "Varians"

msgid "Range"
msgstr "Rentang"

msgid "<em>Note.</em>"
msgstr "<em>Catatan.</em>"

msgid ""
"If not stated otherwise, all values are calculated on a normalized period of "
"2π."
msgstr ""
"Jika tidak dinyatakan, semua nilai dihitung pada periode ternormalisasi 2π."

msgid "Value is shown with respect to the original period."
msgstr "Nilai ditampilkan dengan berdasarkan periode asli."

msgid "Aaron Bahde and Philipp Berens (2019). University of Tuebingen."
msgstr "Aaron Bahde dan Philipp Berens (2019). University of Tuebingen."

msgid ""
"Ulric Lund and Claudio Agostinelli (2017). Circular (Version 0.4-93): "
"Circular Statistics [R Package]."
msgstr ""
"Ulric Lund dan Claudio Agostinelli (2017). Melingkar (Versi 0.4-93): "
"Statistik Melingkar [Paket R]."

msgid "Circular Descriptives Plots"
msgstr "Diagram Deskriptif Melingkar"

msgid ""
"The plotting depends on some of the calculations (e.g. the mean direction). "
"But the calculations returned the following error: %s"
msgstr ""
"Pendiagraman tergantung pada beberapa perhitungan (mis. arah rerata). Tetapi "
"perhitungan mengembalikan galat berikut: %s"

msgid "The plotting for this set-up failed with: %s"
msgstr "Pendiagraman untuk penyiapan ini gagal dengan: %s"

msgid ""
"The data of the dependent variable %1$s grouped on factor %2$s exceeds the "
"tolerance for the concentration. The data shows almost zero variance. Did "
"you maybe specify the wrong period?"
msgstr ""
"Data variabel dependen %1$s digrupkan pada faktor %2$s melampaui toleransi "
"untuk konsentrasi. Data menampilkan hampir nol varians. Apakah Anda mungkin "
"menentukan periode salah?"

msgid "Watson-Williams"
msgstr "Watson-Williams"

msgid "Watson-Wheeler"
msgstr "Watson-Wheeler"

msgid "One-way ANOVA"
msgstr "ANOVA Satu Arah"

msgid "Cases"
msgstr "Kasus"

msgid "Test"
msgstr "Uji"

msgid "p"
msgstr "p"

msgid "F"
msgstr "F"

msgid "df1"
msgstr "df1"

msgid "df2"
msgstr "df2"

msgid "W"
msgstr "W"

msgid "df"
msgstr "df"

msgid "All statistics are calculated on a normalized period of 2%s."
msgstr "Semua statistik dihitung pada periode ternormalisasi 2%s."

msgid ""
"The degrees of freedom of the %1$s%2$s-distribution to which W is compared."
msgstr "Derajat kebebasan dari distribusi-%1$s%2$s yang mana W dibandingkan."

msgid "<em>Warning.</em>"
msgstr "<em>Peringatan.</em>"

msgid ""
"Concentration parameters (%1$s) not equal between the groups of factor %2$s. "
"The Watson-Williams test might not be applicable."
msgstr ""
"Parameter konsentrasi (%1$s) tidak sama antara grup faktor %2$s. Uji Watson-"
"Williams mungkin tidak dapat diterapkan."

msgid ""
"Some groups of factor %s contain less than 10 measurements. The Watson-"
"Wheeler test might not be applicable."
msgstr ""
"Beberapa grup faktor %s berisi kurang dari 10 pengukuran. Uji Watson-Wheeler "
"mungkin tidak dapat diterapkan."

msgid "Two-way ANOVA (Harrison-Kanji Test)"
msgstr "ANOVA Dua Arah (Uji Harrison-Kanji)"

msgid "Sum of Square"
msgstr "Jumlah Kuadrat"

msgid "Mean Square"
msgstr "Rerata Kuadrat"

msgid "Estimated %1$s is %2$s (> 2). The respective routine was run."
msgstr "%1$s terestimasi adalah %2$s (< 2). Rutin terkait telah dijalankan."

msgid "Estimated %1$s is %2$s (< 2). The respective routine was run."
msgstr "%1$s terestimasi adalah %2$s (< 2). Rutin terkait telah dijalankan."

msgid ""
"D. Harrison, G.K Kanji and R. J. Gadsden (2016). Analysis of Variance for "
"Circular Data."
msgstr ""
"D. Harrison, G.K Kanji and R. J. Gadsden (2016). Analisis Varians untuk Data "
"Melingkat."

msgid ""
"The data of the variable %1$s on level %2$s exceeds the tolerance for the "
"concentration. The data shows almost zero variance. Did you maybe specify "
"the wrong period?"
msgstr ""
"Data variabel %1$s pada tingkat %2$s melampaui toleransi untuk konsentrasi. "
"Data menampilkan hampir nol varians. Apakah Anda mungkin menentukan periode "
"salah?"

msgid ""
"The data of the variable %s exceeds the tolerance for the concentration. The "
"data shows almost zero variance. Did you maybe specify the wrong period?"
msgstr ""
"Data variabel %s melampaui toleransi untuk konsentrasi. Data menampilkan "
"hampir nol varians. Apakah Anda mungkin menentukan periode salah?"

msgid "Rao's spacing"
msgstr "Jarak Rao"

msgid "Rayleigh"
msgstr "Rayleigh"

msgid "V against %s"
msgstr "V melawan %s"

msgid "Rao's Spacing"
msgstr "Jarak Rao"

msgid ""
"Estimated %s is infinite, could not compute results. Your data is too "
"concentrated to calculate the assumption check."
msgstr ""
"%s terestimasi tanpa batas, tidak dapat menghitung hasil. Data Anda terlalu "
"terkonsentrasi untuk menghitung pemeriksaan asumsi."

msgid "Uniformity Tests"
msgstr "Uji Keseragaman"

msgid "Variable"
msgstr "Variabel"

msgid "Level"
msgstr "Tingkat"

msgid "Critical"
msgstr "Kritis"

msgid "Statistic"
msgstr "Statistik"

msgid ""
"Gerald Russell and Daniel Levitin (2007). An Extended Table of Probability "
"Values for Raos Spacing Test."
msgstr ""
"Gerald Russell dan Daniel Levitin (2007). Tabel Terluas Nilai Probabilitas "
"untuk Uji Penjarakan Rao."

msgid "The Rao spacing test was run with %1$s = %2$s, %3$s"
msgstr "Uji jarak Rao telah dijalankan dengan %1$s = %2$s, %3$sj"

msgid "Von Mises Assumption Check"
msgstr "Pemeriksaan Asumsi Von Mises"

msgid "Est. %s"
msgstr "Est. %s"

msgid ""
"R. A. Lockhart and M. A. Stephens (1985). Tests of Fit for the Von Mises "
"Distribution."
msgstr ""
"R. A. Lockhart dan M. A. Stephens (1985). Uji Penyesuaian untuk Distribusi "
"Von Mises."

msgid ""
"Do not trust a significant result where %s is small (< 1). The data could "
"rather be uniform."
msgstr ""
"Jangan percaya hasil signifikan di mana %s kecil (< 1). Data kemungkinan "
"dapat berseragam."

msgid ""
"The test is run with %1$s = %2$s, so please compare the statistics to the "
"critical value."
msgstr ""
"Uji dijalankan dengan %1$s = %2$s, jadi silakan bandingkan statistik ke "
"nilai kritis."
